      "body" : "@Ayms:\r\nThe `hdmaster=1` key is the entropy/seed for the BIP32 chain and not the private key at path `m`.\r\nInternally, the seed is stored as a (standard) key, this is why it is also included in the dump. IMO dumping the seed (`hdmaster=1`) can be useful.\r\n\r\nBut the question is, if the term `hdmaster=1` is confusing... maybe `hdseed=1` would be better.",
